        <name>MLZISetProgramLabel</name>
        <param>
          <type>const char *</type>
          <declname>in_label</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Set the human-readable label of the current project or library, to be used in UI display and diagnostic logs to indicate what is running. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>When unset, The Lab and the ZI runtime refer to a program running under ZI by its process / executable name.</para>
<para>A label must be set before the program calls one of the MLGraphicsCreate() functions in order to be reflected.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>API Level:\n 20</title><para></para>
</simplesect>
<parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">in_label</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to a C string indicating the label to use for the running program, or NULL or &quot;&quot; to reset the label. The string is copied. It is interpreted as UTF-8.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<parameterlist kind="retval"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>MLResult_Ok</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>If label was accepted (always).</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<xrefsect id="permissions_1_permissions000738"><xreftitle>Required Permissions</xreftitle><xrefdescription><para>None </para>
</xrefdescription></xrefsect></para>
